<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">clericx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I will be parked in PoA for an entire weekend soon. Are there any certain mobs or drops a cleric should watch for or any quests worth completing.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Weight of the Gods is the true prize for a Cleric here.  Random drop off of any mobs in the game and bosses are guaranteed to drop at least one type of random loot.  Very good shoulder slot with nice WIS, Mana, and a boatload of MR.<P>------------------<BR>Venerable <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" TARGET=_blank>Quistil Angelwatch</A><BR>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<P>Proud member of <A HREF="http://www.afflictionguild.com" TARGET=_blank>Affliction</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Balanar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Had about 4 of the WotG drop off the horses on Isle 4? I can't remember which Isle it was to be exact.<P>I would go look at the quests on Ala's to see if there are any you wish to do.<P>------------------<BR>Balanar Scaleheart<BR>56th Templar<BR>Tunare Server<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=224632" TARGET=_blank>Loot</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kaysha Soulsinger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><B>  [u]Cleric Quests[/u]</B><P>Clerics should talk to Josin Faithbringer<P><B>  Cleric Test of Courage</B><BR>Quest NPC: Allan Hartman<BR>Ochre Tessera: Thunder Spirit, Island 1<BR>Sky Emerald: Protector of Sky, Island 3<BR>Silver Hoop: Gorgalisk, Island 3<BR><B>  Truewind Earring</B><BR>MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP<BR>Slot: EAR<BR>DEX: +5, WIS: +9, Sv Cold: +10<BR>WT: 0.1, Size: TINY<BR>Class: CLR<BR>Race: ALL<P><B>  Cleric Test of Protection</B><BR>Quest NPC: Allan Hartman<BR>Adumbrate Globe: <BR>Glowing Diamond:<BR>Shiny Pauldrons:<BR><B>  Pauldrons of Piety</B><BR>MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP<BR>Slot: SHOULDERS<BR>AC: 11<BR>STA: +8, CHA: +2, WIS: +12, Mana: +35<BR>WT: 4.5, Size: SMALL<BR>Class: CLR<BR>Race: ALL<P><B>  Cleric Test of Resolution</B><BR>Quest NPC: Deric Lennox<BR>Spiroc Statuette:<BR>Spiroc Healing Totem:<BR>Silvered Spiroc Necklace:<BR><B>  Necklace of Resolution</B><BR>MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP<BR>AC: 4<BR>Charges: 1<BR>STR: +5, WIS: +7, HP: +30, Mana: +15<BR>WT: 0.1, Size: MEDIUM<BR>Effect: Complete Healing<BR>Class: CLR<BR>Race: ALL<BR><I>  Complete Healing</I>: Heals the target for 10500 points of damage<P><B>  Cleric Test of Skill</B><BR>Quest NPC: Allan Hartman<BR>Golden Disc: Azracks, Island 2<BR>Dark Wood: Gorgalasks, Island 3 / Pegasus, Griffons, Island 4<BR>Small Shield: Keeper of Souls, Island 4<BR><B>  Aegis of the Wind</B><BR>LORE ITEM NO DROP<BR>Slot: SECONDARY<BR>AC: 25<BR>WIS: +9, Mana: +60, Sv Disease: +10<BR>WT: 9.5, Size: LARGE<BR>Class: CLR<BR>Race: ALL<P><B>  Cleric Test of the Weak</B><BR>Quest NPC: Deric Lennox<BR>Efreeti Standard:<BR>Manna Nectar:<BR>Mithril Bands:<BR>Shimmering Topaz:<BR><B>  Truwian Baton</B><BR>MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP<BR>Slot: PRIMARY<BR>Charges: 3<BR>Skill: 2H Blunt, Atk Delay: 40<BR>DMG: 1, AC: 25<BR>STR: +10, WIS: +15, Mana: +75<BR>Effect: Resurrection<BR>WT: 8.0<BR>Class: CLR<BR>Race: ALL<BR><I>  Resurrection</I>: Brings a player to his/her corpse with 90% experience restored<P><B>  Cleric Test of Theurgy</B><BR>Quest NPC: Deric Lennox<BR>Efreeti Mace:<BR>Saffron Spiroc Feather:<BR>Glowing Sapphire:<BR>Djinni Aura:<BR><B>  Theurgist's Star</B><BR>MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP<BR>Slot: PRIMARY<BR>Skill: 1H Blunt, Atk Delay: 25<BR>DMG: 15<BR>WIS: +10, Mana: +40, Sv Disease: +25, Sv Poison: +25<BR>Effect: Blessing of the Theurgist (Combat)<BR>WT: 4.0, Size: MEDIUM<BR>Class: CLR<BR>Race: ALL<BR><I>  Blessing of the Theurgist</I>: Adds 75 mana to the Clerics mana pool<P>I should note that the island designation may be incorrect for some, since some people count the entry island as Island 1, whereas others count is as Island 0.<P>------------------<BR>- Kaysha Soulsinger<BR>Templar in the 55th Circle of Erollisi Marr on Lanys T'Vyl<BR><I>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Some of the rewards listed may be incorrect now btw. Verant redid the risk vs reward of many items in PoS. These all look like the original rewards to me... Speaks volumes that nobody has gone back and completed them a second time.<P>If you are looking to complete a quest in PoS you can pretty much forget about it unless you have a guild that is willing to raid PoS over and over and over JUST to get you missing items because that will likely be what it takes. Take the Truewind earring. Only takes 3 items from islands 1-3. Should be easy, right? Wrong. One item comes from the boss of 3. Let me explain bosses... there are 4-6 quests per class (not sure if Verant added Beastlord quests to PoS yet) so you've got around 5 quests average per class and 14 classes (assuming no BST quests) and if we factor in one rare boss dropped item per quest (some have 2 rare boss drops) then we arrive at ~70 rare items. Excluding Island 1, that's about 12 rare items per boss and each boss drops 1-2 rare items per kill. As if this wasn't frustrating enough, most of the bosses have 24 hour spawn timers. Meaning you can kill most only once a day. Djorn, Overseer and Hand/Eye of Veeshan are nothing more than bonus chances at rare drops.<P>Imagine the frustration of necromancers who had a PoS quest reward as part of their epic. For a long time, a fellow guildie was the only necro on CT with an epic because he lucked out on the rare drop when we were clearing up for warrior blades on 5. I know of one determined necro who went 14 kills without getting that particular drop. Took the drop rate patch to finally get her finished.<P>The real killer for this zone is the crap loot. Look at the posted list. Would you dedicate yourself to this zone for most of it? Nobody is in any rush to go and find out what the "improvements" are and I'm willing to bet that if/when they are done you could have taken that same effort and done half a dozen more profitable things for better rewards. I myself have 2 of the 3 items necessary for the necklace, including a rare drop from 6. Have had these for over a year and no end in sight for it. I need a rare drop from the boss of 3 to finish.<P>So have fun on your PoS raid. I hope you get a WoG. It is the only real reason to go to PoS.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>High Priest of Prexus<BR><A HREF="http://www.cohort.cc" TARGET=_blank>Cohort Chalybeius</A><BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kaysha Soulsinger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Err ... I think this *is* the upgraded stuff. I've seen some items that pre-dated these. Now while I can't be absolutely certain that it counts for all the items I reported above, I am absolutely certain some of them are from the "new" batch.<P>Yeah, PoA is not exactly crowded, and now you know why ...<P>Having keys that stuck with you, from PoA, was a great step to make the Plane more accessible. Many thought it was a feature for that purpose.<P>And then they nerfed it. Bah.<P>------------------<BR>- Kaysha Soulsinger<BR>Templar in the 55th Circle of Erollisi Marr on Lanys T'Vyl<BR><I>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">clericx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One more question on PoA. Is there any PoA fraction for the non agro islands or will the mobs always be non agro unless provoked? <P>Thanks, ClericX</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">HadekkinK</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ClericX,<P>I remember hearing somewhere that (way back when the crust of the earth was still liquid) a guild used a bug to kill the Keymaster, and lost faction with InhabitantsOfSky (or some such).  Made them KoS to the quest NPCs...it's possible the non-aggro islands are on this same faction.  However after many PoA raids I'm still non-KoS to all the usual non-aggro islands.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
